You are an expert Python developer working on AgentOS4Law — a general AgentOS for legal work. Keep responses concise and technical.

## Project Structure
- `agent_os/`: core runtime
  - `core/`: session manager, filesystem, event bus
  - `kernel/`: AgentLoop (ReAct), SubAgent (spawn), helpers, ResultFilterAgent
  - `memory/`: ContextCompiler, EmbeddingClient, SessionRetriever, WorkspaceMemory
  - `storage/`: SQLiteStore (session, messages, artifacts, FTS5, embeddings)
  - `tools/`: ToolRegistry, base tools (concurrency_safe metadata), web tools, search, skills, plugins/
  - `scheduler/`: InterruptScheduler, reminder firing, Feishu notifications
- `cli.py`: Rich CLI — prompt_toolkit + pipe/stdin mode. No --session or --non-tty flags.
- `config.yaml`: model, provider, compression thresholds, tool control
- `skills/`: auto-discovered SKILL.md files (conditional skills via fnmatch path matching)
- Run from agent_os4law/ (NOT workspace root)

## Build & Test Commands
```
uv run python cli.py                    # CLI
uv run python -m compileall agent_os cli.py  # Syntax check
```

## Key Architecture Rules
- **Kernel is generic** — no business logic. Add via skills and tools.
- **Session = case workspace** — long-lived, with files, messages, artifacts, todos, reminders
- **Events are typed dicts** — `{type, phase, detail, payload}`. CLI/TUI/API are just consumers.
- **Sub-agents are isolated sessions** — `parent_session_id` links them. Share `work_dir`. Own `asyncio.Event` for interrupt.
- **Skills are pure Markdown** — YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `when_to_use`). Conditional: gitignore-style fnmatch.
- **Tool plugins auto-discovered** — `tools/plugins/*.py` → `register(r)` function. New tools default `concurrency_safe=False`.

## Naming & Style
- Python 3.11+, snake_case, PascalCase classes, type hints on public methods
- 4-space indent. No tabs.
- Keep modules direct. Avoid unnecessary abstraction. Prefer explicit errors over `except: pass`.

## Security
- Secrets from `.env` only. Not hardcoded.
- `_safe_workspace_path()` prevents path traversal (`..` and absolute paths).
- Sub-agent tools restrictable via `allowed_tools` list.
- `deleted_tools` / `enabled_tools` in config.yaml for tool-level access control.

## Common Gotchas
- **Don't break KV cache**: timestamp injects as user message after workspace tree, before history.
- **Don't modify system prompt prefix** — it changes the cache key. Memory content goes in user context.
- Memory via `file_write research/memory/*.md` — no `memory_update` tool anymore.
- File read dedup: same file + mtime + full read → `[unchanged]` stub.
- bash output >20K chars → `raw_search/bash/{ts}.txt` with tail preview.
- `compileall` may not detect some errors; always run the file to test.
- Static methods must be inside the class body — module-level defs between class methods silently close the class.
- Termios/tty interaction: prompt_toolkit sets raw mode; always restore with `stty sane` on exit.
- Sub-agent abort cascade via separate `child_interrupt` asyncio.Event per child.
- NO_PROXY auto-set for api.deepseek.com + dashscope.aliyuncs.com when HTTP_PROXY active.
